rComments: Papers are quite easy. Class is mandatory to attend as he covers everything you need to know for the exam and papers. He talks kind of fast and your notes will be quite long but he makes the content kind of bearable.
Good lecturer, talks fast but with clarity. Loves his subject, manages to make Locke and Rousseau somewhat bearable. Essays are supposed to be difficult... not as hard as made out to be.
Very good lecturer. As said before, pay attention and attend the lectures as all of it is a verbal deal. Very engaging! Definitely would have him again

great prof, easy to meet and talk with if you had concerns with anything brought up. You have to be attentive in his class because he's a straight talker, verbal lecture only. Bonus from his class, he hols his own discussion groups with himself and the TA's... I was luckly enough to get one with him. Intelligent prof who can discuss with skill.
Lectures are kind of all over the place. For a first year class there definitely should have been some sort of course notes or even some minimal lecture notes to follow.
Great Prof!! Always willing to help and make sure you understand lectures! Awesome teacher.
Very enthusiastic and helpful - really wanted us to understand the material. Clear lectures, very detailed. Made the class interesting.
